SNA.js

SNA.js is a JavaScript/TypeScript port of the R package `sna` version 2.8 and
is therefore a derivative work of GPL-licensed code. The project is licensed
GPL-2.0-or-later; see LICENSE.

Original package metadata:
- Package: sna
- Version: 2.8
- Title: Tools for Social Network Analysis
- Author/Maintainer: Carter T. Butts
- License: GPL (>= 2)
- CRAN publication date in DESCRIPTION: 2024-09-08
- Source: https://cran.r-project.org/package=sna

Files under src/ that are translations of specific R or C routines carry a
header comment naming the original file and routine (for example,
"Ported from R sna 2.8: R/nli.R `degree` and src/nli.c `degree_R`").

Parity fixtures under fixtures/r-sna-2.8/ are generated outputs produced by
executing the original R package; the generator script records provenance
(R version, sna version, seeds, timestamp) inside the fixture file.

Anyone distributing this library (including bundling it into JavaScript
served to web browsers) must comply with the GPL; see the License section of
README.md for practical notes.
